features: 【Superior Performance】: Class A chip and the superior performance of USB 3.0 are essential storage solutions, with transfer speeds up to 5 times faster than standard USB 2.0 flash drive, making it suitable for schools, businesses or everyday storage of digital data.

【Integrated Design】: The flash drive features an integrated design that prevents the cap from being lost. It is also waterproof, dustproof, shockproof and high temperature resistant. You can hang the flash drive on your work badge or backpack for portable use anytime, anywhere.

【Plug and Play】: No need to install any software, just plug and play. The front of the thumb drive is removable and can be easily opened/closed with your thumb near the flash drive, suitable for work, study or travel.

【Compatible Devices】: The USB 3.0 flash drive supports Windows 7 / 8 / 10 / Vista / XP / 2000 / ME / NT Linux and Mac OS. Compatible with 3.0 ports, compatible with 2.0 and 1.1. Provides high transfer speeds for large files.

【Default Format】: FAT32 is the factory default format and does not support transferring files larger than 4GB. Please format the USB flash drive to exFAT or NTFS according to your needs.[Please backup your data first as it may be lost after formatting.]

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Legit! Good price when on sale.
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a pack of 64 USB 3.0 flash drives in different colors and purchased these as they were on sale forI got mine for $16.74.The USB flash drives come in a nice flat cardboard box, which is sealed with a paper sticker and contains also the "user manual", a sheet reminding us in different languages how to properly use a USB flash drives. The manufacturer makes sure that you feel that you purchased a legit product. So, manual and back of the box are littered with certification logos and contain address, phone number und email address of the manufacturer. The CE and FCC logos are embossed in the drive itself together with the crossed through trashcan.The flash drives look nice, even though the plastic is just average. The sliding mechanism works well and looks durable, but makes them (with 2cm or 0.78") a little wider than some other flash drives I own. Probably not ideal, for those with a tight USB port situation. When in use, you can see a red LED shining through the plastic of the green, yellow and red flash drives. The black or the blue ones stay dark.Oddly, one of the drives appeared on my (Windows 10) system as being write protected by software. I don't know if this was my mistake or if it came like this. However, I was able to solve this with a quick format in no-time. FYI: these flash drives do not have a physical write protection switch.As there are many USB flash drives on the market, which have way lower capacity than advertised. I tested two of these Kexin flash drives with H2testw, which confirmed that they are legit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Does not fit tight.
reviews.reviewText: Quick shipping. Looks nice but didn’t connect easily. When I connected the jump drive is seemed fine but no light, tried a second one, same outcome. Tried another (it was black) no light, have read on a review that the black and blue ones light isn’t very bright. So put another one in still no connection recognized. This time I wiggle it out a bit and seen the light flicker off and on. I then pulled slowly out to where it was barely connected and I finally have a steady light and a recognized flash drive. Over all I probably will send back and buy another brand due to the fact you have to play with connection. I fear that if I bump it, it may disconnect. I have use these drives (not this brand) over many years and have had no problems like this. Hope this was just a bad pack. Good Luck
